law.text:
All information obtained by the department staff or its delegated representative as a result of an investigation made pursuant to this chapter shall not be divulged to anyone except:
Persons suspected of abuse or neglect, provided that in such cases names of informants may be withheld, unless ordered by the court:
Persons within the department or cabinet with a legitimate interest or responsibility related to the case;
Other medical, psychological, social service agency, law enforcement, or other authorized agency that has a legitimate interest in the case;
Cases in which a court orders the release of the information; and
The alleged abused or neglected person.
